snippet: The president said the liberal senator’s warnings about the potential damage of the Trans-Pacific Partnership were nothing more than “hypotheticals.”
abstract: Pres Obama, in online interview, accuses Democratic Sen Elizabeth Warren of Massachusetts of being motivated by politics in opposing Pacific trade accord, deepening conflict with his own liberal base.
lead_paragraph: The president said the liberal senator’s warnings about the potential damage of the Trans-Pacific Partnership were nothing more than “hypotheticals.”

headline.main: Obama Calls Elizabeth Warren ‘Absolutely Wrong’ on Trade Deal
headline.print_headline: Obama Criticizes Liberal Ally Sharply on Pacific Trade Deal
